cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG

The paper presents a novel visualization technique for exploring and presenting large and complex tables, which is likely to fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The technique involves hierarchical aggregation of data subsets, which suggests a possible fit with the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also mentions data selection and filtering capabilities, which could be related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of genomics data for drug discovery may suggest a connection to Deep Learning (cs.DL) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
